+++ DESCRIPTION +++

The script mzTab2report takes mzTab files as input and generates summary pdf reports from its PEP section.

mzTab2report example.mzTab


+++ INSTALLATION +++

(1) install git [1]
(2) clone the repository
    git clone https://github.com/ProteomicsScripts/ProteomicsScripts.git
(3) Install R
    Please check the header of the script which R packages need to be installed [2].    
    Please check that R is in your $PATH [3] i.e. you can run R from the command line [4].
(4) Install LaTeX, tested with MacTeX (macOS), TexLive (Ubuntu 18.04 & 16.04 LTS, sudo apt-get install texlive),
    MiKTeX (Windows). Please check that pdflatex is in your $PATH [2] i.e. you can run pdflatex from the command line [5].
(5) Add the script folder to your system $PATH variable [2].
(6) Test the installation with misc/example_*.mzTab [6]
    
[1] https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/install-git
[2] https://github.com/ProteomicsScripts/ProteomicsScripts/blob/master/mzTab2report/misc/mzTab2report.R#L7
[3] https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PATH_(variable)
[4] https://github.com/ProteomicsScripts/ProteomicsScripts/blob/master/mzTab2report/mzTab2report.bat#L52
[5] https://github.com/ProteomicsScripts/ProteomicsScripts/blob/master/mzTab2report/mzTab2report.bat#L64
[6] https://github.com/ProteomicsScripts/ProteomicsScripts/tree/master/mzTab2report/misc


+++ FILES +++

mzTab2report    -> main script (Linux, macOS)
mzTab2report.bat    -> main script (Windows)
mzTab2report_DragDrop.bat    -> drag-and-drop script, i.e. by dragging an mzTab file onto this batch script the mzTab2report.bat command line tool is executed (Windows)
mzTab2report.Snw    -> Sweave script containing both R and LaTeX code
Sweave.sty    -> Sweave style sheet
misc/example_*.mzTab    -> example input file
misc/example_*.pdf    -> example result file
misc/mzTab2report.R    -> R code from mzTab2report.Snw
